  "standardBio": "Snowpuff, titled among keepers as “Aurora Quietpaw,” carries softened stillness in every movement. Native to Frostveil Basin, the species preserves through powder snow and thin ice, leaving traces that other Riftlings can follow like soft maps. Wild groups form loose bonds rather than rigid packs; a playful individual may become the emotional center of a small hearthline. They eat Frostroot eagerly and dislike food that smells of neglect or spoilage. Ancient keepers carved Snowpuff silhouettes into travel stones, believing the species guided the lost. Modern hatcheries record them as reliable companions; their social intelligence tuned to group moods makes training feel like conversation. Their signature ability, Snowpuff's Frost Bite, reflects a life shaped by Frostveil Basin more than by arena ambition. Many assume Snowpuffs are aggressive because of their frost affinity; most are cautious first. Young Snowpuffs practice Snowpuff's Frost Bite as play long before they understand battle. Adults teach by demonstration: where to rest, what to avoid, how to share warmth or shade.",
  "fullLore": "Snowpuffs first condensed from residual aurorathread along the living edges of Frostveil Basin after early Rift fractures cooled into weather. Their eggs appear where powder snow and thin ice gathers into stillness—never in the loudest danger, always in the pocket of calm beside it. Early surveyors mistook them for ambient phenomena until a Snowpuff returned a dropped lantern, carefully, as if returning a promise.\n\nIn ancient eras, regional peoples treated Snowpuffs as omen-bearers rather than pets. Carvings show them walking ahead of caravans, pausing at unstable ground, and curling around children during ashfall or fog. The species was never “tamed” in the old sense; it chose. That choice culture survives in modern Riftkeeper etiquette: you do not yank a Snowpuff into a bond. You invite, wait, and keep the invitation honest.\n\nModern history is quieter and more practical. Hatcheries map Snowpuff care cycles with the same seriousness given to rare lines, because common does not mean shallow. Frostveil Basin still holds wild populations that trade soft greetings with passerby pets. After major Rift events, Snowpuffs often appear first at recovery centers—not as heroes, but as inventory clerks of comfort, counting who is cold, hungry, or afraid.\n\nNatural behavior is playful at the core and adaptable at the edges. They are shape-fluid and hard to pin, companion-sized, easy to cradle, and communicate through soft chirps and affinity flickers. Socially, they prefer small trusted circles; strangers are assessed by scent, posture, and whether a keeper’s voice stays kind under stress. Intelligence presents as social intelligence tuned to group moods. They sleep in warm stone hollows and prefer weather that matches their affinity’s comfort band.\n\nEcologically, Snowpuffs act as seed dispersers of calm within Frostveil Basin. Allies often include Frostfin and Snowglyph; rivalries with Slagpup and Furnacebeetle are usually about nesting space or shiny refuse, not blood feuds. Predators are rare—most threats come from collapsing terrain and careless machines rather than jaws.\n\nCulture around them is affectionate and slightly superstitious. A collapsed survey team credited their escape to a Snowpuff that chose the only stable ledge in a crumbling pass. Collectors prize unusual cosmetics, yet marketplace notes remind buyers that verified care history matters more than glitter. The common misunderstanding remains: Many assume Snowpuffs are aggressive because of their frost affinity; most are cautious first. The hidden truth keepers debate in soft rooms is simpler and stranger: When deeply bonded, a Snowpuff shares short dream-images of places it has never physically visited.\n\nFrom egg to evolved form, their life story stays continuous. Eggs look like tideglass orbs veined with frost light. Hatchlings are clumsy with sincerity; adults become specialists of place; evolved stages sharpen instinct without erasing childhood habits. Battle tendencies favor swift harassment, and evolution philosophy insists transformation should answer lived experience—not fashion.\n\nFor Riftkeepers, a Snowpuff is a living chapter of Frostveil Basin. Feed it Frostroot, respect its playful tempo, and it will teach you the region’s quieter grammar: which winds lie, which stones remember, which silences are safe. Personal quests often begin with a shell symbol, a remembered scent, or a dream of a door that only opens when the bond is honest. That is the Snowpuff bargain—not destiny sold at rarity price, but a life that continues because you showed up.",
